<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-05-12</DATELINE><TITLE>PCR for Detection of Oseltamivir Resistance Mutation in Influenza A(H7N9) Virus</TITLE><BODY>Sensitive molecular techniques are needed for rapid detection of the R292K oseltamivir-resistant mutant of influenza A(H7/N9) virus strain to monitor its transmission and guide antiviral treatment. We developed a real-time reverse transcription PCR and single nucleotide polymorphism probes to differentiate this mutant strain in mixed virus populations in human specimens.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>